      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"raw and gritty\" vibe makes sense, but I want to get more specific so I don't mess up. When you talk about the \"unapologetically authentic\" part and the stereotypes, what kind of specific look or imagery are you thinking of? Like, if I'm looking for that core \"urban\" identity, what kind of people or specific cultural markers should I be channeling to make sure it's actually grounded in that reality?",
