      "content": "thanks for the breakdown. so you're saying the aesthetic is basically tied to these specific racial groups? if i'm trying to design something that captures that \"inner city\" energy, are you saying the \"real\" version of this style is fundamentally different from, say, high-fashion or more \"mainstream\" streetwear? like, is there a specific \"look\" that distinguishes a person from an urban background vs someone else just wearing the clothes?",
